&lt;&lt;&gt; AzureBlade displayed some sort of friendly smile. Of course, being 
&gt; totally transmetal did not help the motion, but he managed it.
&gt; 
&gt; AzureBlade: We are on prehistoric Earth. There is a war going on, and 
&gt; there is a battle not far from here. You can check your sensors for 
&gt; confirmation. I, however, am not implicated in this battle. I came 
&gt; here directly for you. I felt your spark and...
&gt; 
&gt; Suddenly he was out of words. How should he say this? Of course, he 
&gt; was a warrior, tall, strong and proud. How could he say anything 
&gt; without making her go crazy at him? This was the first time it 
&gt; happened to him.&gt;&gt;

Prehistoric Earth...was that where she was? And a war as well...that meant 
there were more on this planet. In a way, she was glad...but in a way, she 
had almost hoped not to discover such a thing. Was she to have to fight as 
well? Without knowing what side she was on? Who her allies were? And her 
enemies...what if AzureBlade turned out to be...

&quot;I see..&quot; she said quietly. At least she had nothing to fear from him yet. 
Unless it turned out he was, she wouldn&#39;t consider him a threat..he didn&#39;t 
seem to pose her any, as he&#39;d said. She smiled slightly &quot;Thank you.&quot;

&gt; 
&gt; &lt;&lt;AzureBlade: The fact is I am a Maximal, and, if you would like, you 
&gt; can join my faction. By the way, what is your faction?&gt;&gt;

That was a question she had been somewhat dreading. &quot;My faction? 
Well..I...I&#39;m not sure.&quot; Her ears flickered, annoyed at herself once again 
&quot;My memory was partially damaged somehow...I don&#39;t remember.&quot;

